@NODE INTRODUCTION "INTRODUCTION"
Here it is! Long-expected(?) new set of bitmap fonts by Heikki Kantola aka
Hezu. 
And if you ask why I'm still making bitmap fonts, the aswer is simple: Nobody
has bought me TypeSmith (the person who does so, will get his/her name
printed with very big letters in documentation of the next HKFonts volume ;))
:(

The Fonts included are:

@{" 2002 " Link 2002}
@{" Cubic " Link Cubic}
@{" Militant " Link Militant}
@{" Scriptum " Link Scriptum}
@{" Shark " Link Shark}
@{" Skinny Shark " Link Skinny_Shark}
@{" X-CommII " Link X-CommII}
@ENDNODE

@NODE 2002 "2002"
 Futuristic non-proportional font. Size: 16x8
 Nice as X-Comm terminal font on laced screen. :)

@ENDNODE

@NODE Cubic "Cubic"
 Another futuristic font. This time in 7x7 size.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Militant "Militant"
 Name tells all... Proportional, sizes: 11 and 16.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Scriptum "Scriptum"
 Old-looking proportional font in 16 point size.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Shark "Shark"
 11 point version is infact a rerelease (as it was included in HKFonts4
 too), but as I'm too lazy (it's easier to add both sizes ;)) it is included in
 this archive with scaled down 8 point sized version.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Skinny_Shark "Skinny Shark"
 11 point @{" Shark " Link Shark} went to diet and this is the result. Suits laced screens
 bit better.

@ENDNODE

@NODE X-CommII "X-CommII"
 This is almost the same 8 point font that I've made for @{" X-Comm " Link X-Comm}, but I
 disliked 'T' and so I redesigned it and now it looks better IMHO.

@ENDNODE

